place_description: Seattle-based coffeehouse chain known for its signature roasts, light bites and WiFi availability.

reviews_data.review_text: Great friendly staff!

Great atmosphere!

Located in a plaza with other shops.

Each time I come here, my coffee will always cost more then every where else I've been going. Come to find out, they are charging me triple the amt for the syrup when I NEVER even ask for anything extra, which is a rip-off. I will no longer be coming here.
Please take a look at your app when using it. I didn't realize it until today.
Nice environment...

Love this location of Starbucks.
Nikki is an excellent human being. She is beautiful inside and out. She helps all the customer with warmth. I hope Starbucks notices her efforts and excellent customer service.
I literally love this starbucks the workers are very sweet very informative when I'm in need of something new no complaints.

Very dry customer service...the young lady seemed like she didn't want to be there. I went through the drive thru and was asked "What can I get you?"....What happened to "Hi, welcome to Starbucks. What can I get for you?"

I would have given this place a one but you have a worker in there.Her name is Taylor she is that girl.She is that 1 she is that superstar.No one else would speak to me or help me.But taylor was on point. She is.
Definitely.An asset to this company and she is definitely the one keeping customers coming back

DRIVE-THRU Cashier is the driest person ever!   Asked for a coffee frap with whip, and he told me I can't have whip!!!!  Excuse me?  His dry attitude was not an isolated occurrence.   He's like this everytime I come and he's working the drive thru.
There are Starbies closer to me but I choose this one only because of SAM.

I mean, it's Starbucks. Does it need another review?
understaffed
The manager was horrible, 3rd time bad experience

Had to go home and make my own coffee! Do not bother placing a mobile order here. Waited 20 mins AFTER leaving the drive through line bc I sat there for 10 and it didn't move. Luckily the line was so long I was outside of the parking lot and could leave. Everyone else was stuck. The items in my order came out 10 mins apart so my frappe was melted and egg bites cold. Im they didn't even call out my name for the eggs bites and didn't put them on the customer side of the counter, luckily I saw my name and grabbed them from the other side AFTER they were sitting there for idk how long.

Crystell  fue muy amable conmigo y es agradable la buena atencion.
Las bebidas estaban perfectas gracias.
Siempre voy a esta tienda.
That atmosphere is horrible.  Very hard wooden chairs as if they don't want you there.

Employee are super rude and completely encored me as I was trying to receive my order for the night. Had to leave without my order and wait til the next day. I've even walked thru the drive way to reach someone attention by the manager I believed just encores me and walks to the back as of she can't see me

Lived the new store design. Modern exterior,  stylish furniture with tables for spreading out.
It was noisy, however, with few customers inside. Probably the open space, high ceiling design.

waited 20 minutes for a mobile order (1 drink). 15 of those were in store past my pickup time. employees wouldn't even look at me. not my first experience like this at this location. order was very clearly wrong when they gave it to me. ordered a java chip frap and the drink was vanilla colored and nasty. it just tasted like caramel and ice. i felt bad asking but still got it remade in the drive through and had to wait an additional 10 minutes for my remake which at least tasted good! my pickup was at 11:59 and i did not leave the location until 12:32. i'm actually so confused as to what takes so long at this location because it is not busy.

This store is embarrassingly slow compared to other locations that I've been to in Charlotte. Ordered a drink thru the app and it took nearly 30 minutes for them to make. Only location in the area where I've had this issue. Definitely wouldn't recommend if you're on a schedule.

Today was my last trip to Starbucks. This store especially never pays attention nor makes drinks to Starbucks recipe standards. I've had previous problems with this store and the district manager was supposed to reach out to me and never did! The app is deleted and they have officially lost two customers for life!

They need new management.  The store was suppose to open at 5am. We pulled up at 5:15am. The door was unlocked but once we opened the door, two employees said they are not open. "Why?" They said all employees arrived late. We asked, "How long until they are ready?" 30 minutes. OK, can I use your restroom? Lady said very rudely,  "No, we are closed." She locked the door as we left.
Not open when store hours are posted because employees can't make it to work on time.

I was looking forward to this new place opening. Its very convenient for me. It's larger with large covered patio. But I'm disappointed. Service is below par. Not real friendly, the temp is cold, low lighting, and wi-fi doesn't work. Staff said it's spotty connectivity. What!? This is a place where many people go to use their computer. You have to do better.
My favorite place ! :)

I used to love the old location and once the new one opened up I was really excited hoping to love it. Unfortunately the service is really rude and would purposely not make a drink until you wait more than 10 minutes this is without anyone else waiting for a drink. The drive through was also empty when I came. I am very courteous when I come in but receive the opposite. The drink is also not made with the things I paid extra for and they get upset if I ask for the caramel or whip but if they were made correctly I would not have a need to remind them. I really really have been thinking about just taking a pause from Starbucks.

Idk if it's because of the location change, but it truly is a hit or miss with service and product. The service has just gone down extremely. Even if you come in there, as kind as you can be, the girl at the front is always extremely rude and careless about what they are serving.

THIS STARBUCKS HAS NO WIFI

The Wi-Fi technically "connects" but you can't access anything.  Even the baristas know this but haven't put a sign on the door giving you a heads-up.  It would have been nice to know this before placing my order in preparation for sitting here to study for hours.  I formerly worked for Starbucks and it was standard practice to put a note on the door anytime the WiFi was down.
The staff are amazing!!! And make me feel so welcome whenever I'm in there it's just unfortunate that the customers in the lobby are creeps and weirdos.

I really want to commend this staff and service providers at this location. I think you all are doing a great job with becoming a drive thru location actually the only drive thru on Wt Harris on the west end! To have increased with so many new customers and adding yet another skill to the store a Drive Thru is phenomenal. I know once you can master and Accommodate all the new comers and level of busy you all have been. This store will surpass 100% and appeal. If anyone reading reviews and leaving reviews can give this great staff a moment to adjust the store, service, and cleanliness with fall in place naturally. I want all the staff to know I appreciate you all. And congratulations on the new store and drive thru.

This is a brand new Starbucks and it is FILTHY.  The floor, the tables, chairs... and let's talk about the bathroom.  I was shocked.  Spilled coffee on the floor of the Bathroom - NO toilet tissue, the sink and the mirror were disgusting.  I couldn't believe it.  Fingure prints all over ever glass door.  Not what I expected - at all.  Hire a cleaning service - something... DO BETTER!

I pass 2-3 other Starbucks locations just to make it to this one. Shayland, Rai, and Nikki always make it such a personable experience. Their ability to balance all of the chaos and still squeeze in a genuine smile, always warms my heart!

If you haven't yet been to the new Davis Lake Starbucks, stop missing out!!!
If I could give this Starbucks location a zero, I would. Worse customer service on the planet. Slow as molasses!! New building. Old horrible service!! Ridiculous

Just left the drive thru 9/15/23 at 8:14am. I didn't care for the cashiers attitude or smart comment when I asked if my points were redeemed to substitute the milk. Come to find out after driving off, my points weren't redeemed. The cashier should work on improving her communication, listening, and professionalism skills. You never know who is watching because she was terrible. Also, my caramel cappuccino was not good.

The people that work there are very rude when it comes to customers. I was working Uber eats and had a order there just a few minutes ago. They had me waiting for almost 10 minutes without telling me that my order was ready sitting at the end of the line While I was sitting down waiting. Very unprofessional and unorganized and also lack communication. Cashier seems to not care about herself or her job, her attitude was deplorable and standoffish. I don't even like Starbucks but I will never go back to that location ever again if I was to ever think about dinning at Starbucks.

I come here to get coffee and door dash and when I DoorDash they never ask me or other dashers what order did you have and I feel like it's there job to ask how can I help you. Not one said anything or even looked at me. Turns out the order I've been waiting on is already ready and has been ready for a while. When I order coffee the coffee was wrong twice and had no sugar. I've never been disappointed with a Starbucks before this experience has upset me greatly.
Literally the best Starbucks. All of the employees are wonderful. 9/10 they know who I am and they're always so friendly. My drinks and food are always perfect.

Got there at 8:38 for my quick coffee before work on Aug 20th... you see they saw me coming as the building is all glass and completely ignored when online closing says at 9pm.
I then drove to the drive thru along with other cars I was completely ignored and I was also trying to let them know there was a baby puppy or kitten couldn't tell in the drive thru that could be ran over ( random but true literally in the middle of the drive thru ) wanted them to at least notice  that wasn't safe. They quickly ran to lock the drive thru doors and just kind of looked at me and laughed and ran away! As a loyal Starbucks costumer I am so disappointed with the costumer service. I can understand wanting to clean up but one hot coffee wouldn't have hurt ? And to act as if I'm completely not standing there while they still had people sitting outside was insane . We then called at 8:45 the store to ask "hey you see me standing here why are you closed 20 minutes early and laughing about it ?" But they didn't even pick up. What's worse is this is my local Starbucks and a new one and now I don't even want to ever go there again!!

Excellent service and atmosphere and most importantly THE PEOPLE!!!!

I ordered 4 boxes of coffee for an event and picked up and even had help offered to bring the 4 boxes, big bag of cups and different sweeteners/sugars and stirring sticks and a half gallon for creamer.

The best service ever! And it was like 8am on a Saturday morning!!!!!!!
Well staffed. Lots of workers, so items go out quickly. Good standards. Local folks in the area slightly strange however.
Staff very loud yelling across the store. Very unprofessional. Date on 6/7/23 at 6:49pm.
I wanted green tea frappe.. well they didn't have the product and she couldn't tell me what would be similar..
I just left the drive-thru and I was met with the rudest male cashier , it was unbelievable. I've never been so dissatisfied with customer service especially at this location.

Didn't like this Starbucks.... Customer service is okay... I went in with no lines inside and only 2 cars in the drive thru... why did it take about 10 mins to get my 1 drink order.... I'm used to Starbucks being fast especially when it's slow... they had at least 4 ppl behind the counter. But on the bright side the new store looks great!!!!
Really friendly and polite.

Great visit on 3/13/23. I got my normal complexed frappe order.  The gentleman picked up the cup and let out a small sigh.  I laughed inside. Once he finished, the drink was beautiful.  He took his time and made sure it was made to perfection.  I told him " I could tell that was my cup by the sigh."  We laughed and he said it was no problem.  Went back to the car and got a tip. He was very appreciative! Service was so great I had to call the store and get his name. Thank you Mannie for making my experience magical! Nothing feels better than to spend your money, and receive a superb product accompanied by the same level of customer service.
Another good Starbucks

Shayla "the manager" is very dismissive, picking her nose, on her watch responding to messages, trying to make coffee without washing her hands. We were regulars at this store and TODAY was the most despicable experience we have ever experienced from a Starbucks location or employee. I really hope the district manager or someone of upper management views this review. Because the supposed manager needs to be suspended for that behavior without pay. If she don't like her job she should just quit. Not make someone else's experience miserable because she's having a bad day. My wife and I ordered a couple coffees and they were not made to order because the order was never taken correctly. I will definitely take my experience as far as I need to in order to have this handled. I'm livid!!

11/11 Generally, I go inside and bypass the drive thru, but i had my kids and wanted to grab a quick coffee. We  waited in the drive thru line for 15 real life  mins on a Saturday afternoon because the orders for the people in front of us were wrong. This is not a drive thru that you can leave once you've gone in-unless there aren't cars behind you (the driveway is bordered with bricks on both sides). When we finally got to the window the barista didn't apologize and when we suggested that in the future, if they get a patrons drink order wrong, they should tell them to drive up and then bring them the correct order when it's ready instead of keeping 6 cars in the drive thru line captive, he responded with "we don't have a protocol for that...". Whether you have a "protocol" or not, keeping 6 cars stuck in line for 15 mins should not be your default. It's extremely inconvenient and not mindful of your customers time. Disappointing.
